 {"id": "franken_networkx-nvsetcmp", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] NodeView missing Set subset/superset comparison operators", "description": "nx.NodeView inherits from collections.abc.Set and therefore supports ``G.nodes <= {0,1}``, ``G.nodes >= other``, and strict ``<``/``>`` comparisons. fnx's Rust-native NodeView only inherits Mapping, so ``G.nodes <= some_set`` raised TypeError. Added __le__/__ge__/__lt__/__gt__ methods mirroring collections.abc.Set mixin semantics, and registered NodeView as a virtual subclass of Set so ``isinstance(G.nodes, Set)`` is also True. Verified comparisons match nx on all four directions (view vs set, set vs view) across all four graph classes.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T17:00:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T17:00:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T17:00:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Add Set mixin methods + virtual subclass registration", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-evsetcmp", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] EdgeView (all 4 graph types) missing Set subset/superset comparisons", "description": "Same root cause as br-nvsetcmp but affecting EdgeView / _DiGraphEdgeView / _MultiGraphEdgeView / _MultiDiGraphEdgeView. nx's EdgeView inherits collections.abc.Set and supports ``{(0,1)} <= G.edges`` etc. fnx's edge views only had __eq__/__ne__/__or__/__and__/__sub__/__xor__ but not the comparison operators. Added them across all four Rust/Python edge-view classes and registered each as a virtual Set subclass.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T17:00:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T17:00:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T17:00:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Add Set mixin methods + registration across all 4 types", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-multiiterkeys", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] MultiGraph/MultiDiGraph edge view default iteration yielded 2-tuples; nx yields 3-tuples with keys", "description": "nx.MultiEdgeView's default __iter__ returns 3-tuples ``(u, v, key)``. The ``G.edges()`` call form defaults to 2-tuples (keys=False). fnx's _MultiGraphEdgeView.__iter__ and _MultiDiGraphEdgeView.__iter__ both delegated to ``iter(self())`` (keys=False), yielding 2-tuples and thus collapsing parallel edges. Set comparisons ``G.edges <= {...}``, iteration counts, and downstream consumers that rely on 3-tuples diverged from nx. Fix: __iter__ now calls ``self(keys=True)``; the ``G.edges()`` call-form default (keys=False) is unchanged.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T17:00:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T17:00:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T17:00:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Default iter to keys=True", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-louvainquality", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] louvain_communities returned suboptimal partition (Rust missed second-phase aggregation)", "description": "Louvain is a two-phase iterative modularity maximizer \u2014 Phase 1 moves nodes between communities; Phase 2 collapses each community to a super-node and re-runs Phase 1; iterate until convergence. The Rust _raw_louvain_communities only did Phase 1 once, yielding a markedly lower-quality partition than nx. On karate_club_graph: fnx returned 2 communities {16, 18} with modularity ~0.4036 for every seed tested, while nx returned 4 communities {4, 6, 10, 14} with modularity ~0.4266-0.4439. Route fnx.louvain_communities through _louvain_impl which delegates to nx.algorithms.community.louvain_communities via _call_networkx_submodule_for_parity so fnx matches nx's partition quality.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T17:30:00.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T17:30:00.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T17:30:00.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Delegate to nx's hierarchical Louvain", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
